The article announces several nominations and appointments made by President Donald J. Trump. 

1. Nathan A. Simington has been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Communications Commission. He currently serves as a Senior Advisor in the National Telecommunications and Information Administration (NTIA), specializing in network and telecommunications policy.

2. Lieutenant General Eric P. Wendt has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the State of Qatar. He currently serves as Commander of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization Special Operations Headquarters.

3. Michael Rigas has been nominated to be Deputy Director for Management, Office of Management and Budget. He currently serves as the Acting Director of the United States Office of Personnel Management.

4. Joyce Campbell Giuffra has been nominated to be a Member of the National Council on the Arts. She has held senior positions in government, corporate public relations, and nonprofit organizations.

In addition to these nominations, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint the following individuals to key positions:

1. Arthur Kleinschmidt, Ph.D., to be Deputy Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy.

2. Alejandro Sanchez to be a Member of the President's Export Council.

3. Vinson X. Palathingal to be a Member of the President's Export Council.

4. David Tamasi to be a Member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee.

5. Eduardo Verastegui to be a Member of the President's Advisory Commission on Hispanic Prosperity.

6. Steven Gatena to be a Member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council.

7. Dr. Rick Rader to be a Member of the National Council on Disability.